item.dc:creator: shaq
item.content:encoded:
Let Us Solve For You

  • James Leonard has 15 years professional experience in management and IT. He is an experience systems engineer, program manager, web and software developer, and focuses on using business process improvement. James holds a bachelors of general studies from UCONN, a bachelors in Technology Management from Kansas State, a bachelors of science in business administration from the University of Tennessee, a Masters of Engineering from Catholic University of America, a Masters of Policy Management from Georgetown University, and a MBA from University of North Carolina, Chapel Hill. James is married to his wife Jenny and father to Conor, Evelyn, and Nathaniel.

Customers don’t stop acquiring a service or product, they stop working with managers that fail to ensure expectations are met or exceeded. Evlos management continuously strives to improve the services and products provided by Evlos Technology. We understand the trust and responsibility owed to our customers, employees, and all stakeholders contributing to the Evlos value chain.

Established in 2012, Evlos Technology provides: Systems and Software Engineering, Systems Engineering and Technical (SETA) Services, Business Process Reengineering, IT Project Management, and Executive Level Staff Support.

item.dc:creator: shaq

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: Management Professionals employ business management best practices to assist organizations to rapidly scale their IT service offerings, reduce cost and complexity, or migrate legacy services to industry leading standards. Technology management techniques are utilized to improve tactical daily operations as well as to forecast and adopt innovative technology improvements, policy changes, and general management environment changes. We work to align these changes with the customer mission and functions so that they are not a disruption, rather they are harnessed in manner that improves their products and services.

Systems engineering best practices are essential to implementing significant technological, process, and organizational changes. The Evlos Technology team works directly with the customer to identify opportunities and capitalizes on these by working with the appropriate stakeholders to capture inputs, activities, and outputs in order to implement an efficient and effective end user system. Evlos Technology professionals are knowledgeable in gathering customer functional requirements, translating them to technical requirements, and designing improvements based off these requirements.

Evlos provides design, development, testing and evaluation, implementation, maintenance and improvement services and products for cloud computing and IT efforts. Evlos specializes in each of these respective life cycle activities to provide the intended results across a mission activity. Evlos’ distinct experience allows for the mitigation of issues prior to their inception whether the effort is a migration to a cloud environment or standing up a new service in a cloud environment.

Evlos Technology is dedicated to continuously improve our products and services to increase our value to the customer and their mission. Business Process Re-Engineering and total quality management methods are applied to our products and services. We will be efficient and effective in everything we do.
